Overflow

1. Overflow is a property that sets the desired 
behavior when content does not quite fit 
in the parent element box meaning it overflows.

2. There’re 5 states:
        1. overflow: visible
        2. overflow: hidden
	       Any content that will overflow 
           outside of the bow will be hidden

        3. overflow: clip
        4. overflow: scroll
           Our box will contain the scroll bar 
           both horizontal and vertical. 
           We can use the scroll bar to see 
           the entire length of content. 
           We still have the scroll bar,
           although it’s disabled (the content
           fit in the box).

        5. overflow: auto 
           Like scroll, but we don’t see the scroll bar 
           until we do need it (the content doesn't
           fit in the box).

example
#file index.html

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <title>Document</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="style.css">
</head>

<body>
    <div>    
        <p>Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet consectetur 
        adipisicing elit. Hic illum ea, tempora 
        inventore sint, corrupti, officia sed beatae 
        aut qui illo provident repudiandae voluptas 
        at dolor. A perferendis recusandae 
        laboriosam.</p>
    </div>
 
</body>
</html>


#file style.css

div{
    border: solid;
    height: 50px;
    overflow: auto;
}

